European, Asian Stocks Decline as Moody’s Raises Greek Debt Default Risk

-- B y   J a s o n   C a r e y
-- 
2011-06-02T07:06:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/european-asian-stocks-decline-as-moody-s-raises-greek-debt-default-risk.html
European stocks slumped as  Greece ’s
risk of default was raised to 50 percent by Moody’s Investors
Service and amid concern that the global economic recovery is
faltering. Asian shares also fell while U.S. index futures rose.  BHP Billiton Ltd. and Rio Tinto Group declined as base
metal prices retreated. Kingfisher Plc, Britain’s biggest home-
improvement retailer, fell as profit missed estimates. Amlin
Plc, the biggest Lloyd’s of  London  insurer by market value,
declined as Morgan Stanley downgraded its recommendation on the
stock.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index sank 0.8 percent to 276.27 as of
8:03 in London. The MSCI Asia Pacific Index retreated 1.8
percent. European markets including Switzerland, Austria and
Sweden are closed today for the Ascension Day holiday. Standard
& Poor’s 500 Index futures expiring this month rose 0.2 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jason Carey at 
 jcarey3@bloomberg.net  